# Package.json script naming

Use **`subject:verb`** with optional **`:qualifier`** segments. Keep scripts alphabetically sorted by key in `package.json`.

## Format

| Pattern | Example |
|---------|---------|
| `subject:verb` | `daisy:build`, `app:test`, `e2e:test:ui` |
| `deploy:<type>:<verb>` | `deploy:docker:build`, `deploy:aws-ec2:docker-run`, `deploy:gcp:push` |
| `ci:<area>:<verb>` | `ci:pages:copy-404` |

## Subjects

- **`app`** — repo-wide entrypoints (`app:build`, `app:dev`, `app:lint`, `app:test`)
- **Feature/domain** — `daisy`, `lang`, `cli`, `notepop`, `e2e`, `vosk-model`, …
- **`ci`** — CI-only pipeline glue (not shared dev workflows)
- **`deploy`** — Docker, VM, and cloud ops (`deploy:<type>:<verb>`)
- **`docs`** — documentation tooling

## Verbs (second segment, or last for `deploy:`)

`build`, `test`, `render`, `run`, `dev`, `calibrate`, `loop`, `regen`, `bench`, `bundle`, `compile`, `ensure`, `install`, `check`, `lint`, `clear`, `preview`, `analyze`, `sloc`, `shell`, `copy-404`, …

## Examples

```json
// ✅ GOOD
"app:build": "yarn vosk-model:ensure && vite build",
"daisy:build": "sh zss/feature/synth/backend/daisy/native/build-daisy.sh",
"notepop:test:full": "yarn daisy:build && yarn notepop:render:ab && yarn notepop:test",
"deploy:aws-ec2:docker-run": "sh scripts/aws-ec2-docker-run.sh",
"ci:pages:copy-404": "cp .github/404.html ./cafe/dist"

// ❌ BAD — verb-first
"build:daisy": "…",
"test:notepop": "…",
"render:sidechain:ab": "…"

// ❌ BAD — deploy without type segment
"deploy:build": "…"
```

## Exceptions

- **npm lifecycle hooks** keep npm names (`postinstall`, `prepublishOnly`, …)
- Composite scripts must chain **new** script names only

## When adding scripts

1. Pick subject first (what is being acted on)
2. Pick verb second (the action)
3. Add qualifiers only when needed (`:full`, `:ab`, `:fxmatrix`)
4. Insert alphabetically in `package.json`
